<dl id="n34002e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n34" href="#n34002e">N34 (VI.B.27)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n34all.htm#n34002e"> 2(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> paleologus <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n34002e"> <li>FW isotext 572.19 </li><li><ms href="#n34002e">MS BL 47485-48</ms> </li><li>JJA 60:326 <a name="sd4" href="../../FF/fdra/sda.htm#sd4">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/s/sd4.htm#n34002e">Draft: III&sect;4.4</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">The negotiations at the council of Lyons (1274) were, strictly speaking, between the pope and the Byzantine emperor, and were more political than ecclesiastical. <mark>Michael Palaeologus</mark> ruled in Constantinople while Baldwin II., the last of the Latin emperors, was in exile in Europe.. Paleologus wished the pope to acknowledge his title to be emperor of the East, and in return promised submission to the papal supremacy and the union of the two churches on the pope&apos;s own terms. This enforced union lasted only during the lifetime of the emperor. <small> &ldquo;ORTHODOX EASTERN CHURCH&rdquo; <a name="EBOEC" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBOEC"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 335 [Attempts at reunion]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
